      <hr />
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <div class="definition">
         <div>
            <p>Geographic name that is equivalent to the 151 geographic name or 181 geographic
               subdivision field of the same record. It links headings within a system or from
               different thesauri or authority files.
            </p>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <div class="guidelines">
         <div>
            <p>Most of the content designators defined for field 751 are the same as those defined
               for
               field 151 (Heading-Geographic Name), field 451 (See From Tracing-Geographic Name),
               and
               field 551 (See Also From Tracing-Geographic Name). Description, guidelines, and input
               conventions for shared content designators are given in the <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/adx51.html">X51 Geographic Names-General Information</a></em> section.
            </p>
            <p>Guidelines for applying the second indicator, subfield $w (Control subfield),
            subfield $2 (Source of heading or term), subfield $i (Relationship information),
               and subfield $4 (Relationship code) in field 751 are given in the <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ad7xx.html">7XX Heading Linking Entries-General Information</a></em> section.
            </p>
         </div>
